  "text": "A major strength of the study was that findings were nationally representative for the USA. NIS data is a large deidentified inpatient database, and our study has good statistical power. The APR-DRG coding systems used in this study to assess the severity of illness and risk of mortality are externally validated. They are very reliable and consistent, and widely used by hospitals, consumers, payers and regulators [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
